The related influenza search terms were ranked first and those terms that having no data within one calendar year during the study period were excluded. Pearson correlation analysis was performed to explore the correlation between influenza-related search queries and the reported number of influenza cases in Liaoning. Those search terms that with the statistically significant correlation coefficient above 0.4 were sent to the construction of SVM regression model. The selection of maximum cross-correlation coefficient has been proposed in previous studies (
 Guo et al., 2017a; 
 Yuan et al., 2013).
